title: OR: $45 million data center could open at Eastern Oregon Regional Airport
text:
05 OR: $45 million data center could open at Eastern Oregon Regional Airport 
Oregonian: According to a report written by Economic Development Director Steve Chrisman to the city council for its Tuesday meeting, staff needs council approval to finalize a 30-year lease with Makad Corp. to build a $45 million colocation data center on nearly 12 acres on Airport Road halfway between Northwest 56th Street and Stage Gulch Road.
